# Bedrock POC — HTTP Test Requests
# Run the app first: dotnet run --launch-profile http
# Scalar API reference: http://localhost:5015/scalar/v1

@host = http://localhost:5015
@hostHttps = https://localhost:7271

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Extract document using Claude 3 Sonnet (default keys)
###    Sends a PDF, lets the API use the configured DefaultKeys.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/documents/Claude35Sonnet
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="File"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
------boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. Extract document using Claude 3 Sonnet (custom keys)
###    Overrides DefaultKeys with a focused subset.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/documents/Claude35Sonnet
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="File"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[0]"

First Party
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[1]"

Second Party
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[2]"

Filing Date
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[3]"

Parcel ID
------boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Extract document using Cohere Command Light (default keys)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/documents/CommandLight
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="File"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
------boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. Extract with a custom prompt template
###    {keyList} is replaced by the API with the formatted keys.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/documents/Claude35Sonnet
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="File"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Prompt"

<System>
You are a legal document analyst. Extract each <element> from <information> found in the <document>.
Return a JSON array where each object has: key, value, startPosition, score.
If a field is not found set startPosition to -1.
<information>{keyList}</information>
Output must be valid JSON only, no explanation.
</System>
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[0]"

Case Number
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[1]"

Property Address
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[2]"

Grantor
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Keys[3]"

Grantee
------boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. Validation error — missing file (expect 400)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/documents/Claude35Sonnet
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6. Validation error — unknown model enum value (expect 400)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/documents/UnknownModel
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="File"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
------boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7. HTTPS variant — same as #1 but via the HTTPS profile
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{hostHttps}}/documents/Claude35Sonnet
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="File"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
------boundary--

###
